      "title": "Minimax theorems and their proofs",
      "abstract": "We suppose that X and Y are nonempty sets and f: X x Y \u2192IR A minimax theorem is a theorem which asserts that, under certain conditions, ::: ::: $$\\mathop{{\\min }}\\limits_{Y} \\mathop{{\\max }}\\limits_{X} f = \\mathop{{\\max }}\\limits_{X} \\mathop{{\\min }}\\limits_{Y} f.$$"
